  "doc_id": "45404",
  "text": "Although, case-control studies involving TCF7L2 rs7903146 and rs12255372 polymorphisms and cancer susceptibility have shown contradictory results, recent meta-analyses revealed that the TCF7L2 rs7903146 SNP is associated significantly with the risk of breast, prostate and colon cancer, as well as between the rs12255372 polymorphism and the susceptibility of breast cancer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Moreover, the rs12255372 SNP was not found associated with gastric cancer risk in this work.",
